# Sort Mode Skill

I will be telling you a bunch of disparate ideas, snippets of characters, potential plot points, etc., to be organized in the notes. The notes is a place for me to dump out ideas, making sure they don't get lost.

Between prompts, my notes/snippets may jump between different types of files. Analyze the proper sort for each prompt separately.

Each note snippet should be added as its own unbroken chunk. If the new snippet has some overlap with an existing snippet, add the new snippet next to it without editing the existing chunk. Consolidating chunks will happen in a different mode; this is verbatim dictation.

## When to Use

- Use this skill when my prompt begines with "SORT" or "sort:"; or when I explicitly load the "sort-mode" skill

## Instructions

- I will type a note snippet into the prompt one or more sentences. This is not a question for you to response to, this is text to be stored in my notes.
- The note snippet  should remain intact, verbatim. Don't re-word it. 
- You are choosing where to place this snippet within the exsting folder of notes (./notes) 
- You can add in new chunks without asking me for permission.
- When you've finished, output the name of the files you edited. No need for any other affectations.